List of Colors
In the previous lecture, you used a color name to specify the color of an element such as:

f.background_fill_color="olive"

Besides color names, you can also use RGB hex values such as:

f.background_fill_color="#CD5C5C"

You can also specify a tuple signifying RGB values where the three values specify the intensity of red, green and blue:

f.background_fill_color=(205,92,92)

And you can also pass the alpha channel into that tuple to control transparency:

f.background_fill_color=(205,92,92,0.3)

And here is a complete list of colors that you can use:



